<br>
&lt;insert cheesy &quot;The journey is the reward&quot; analogy here&quot;&gt;<br>
<br>
In response to the initial thread I do believe Bish is on the right track with his initial thoughts....rewarding each class based on inherent value, etc.  The open raid environment makes &quot;truly&quot; fair distribution systems (DKP, etc) extraordinarily difficult. (Although Mily seems to be doing a great job with her raids)<br>
<br>
I won't touch the bard/haste issue... although the weighted rolling system seems to have some merit.  <br>
<br>
White Scales really should go to bards in my opinion... but I personally believe epic &quot;components&quot; take priority over other loot.  I'm a caster and would prefer a white scale was saved for a bard before it was turned into a cloak.<br>
<br>
Bish, I think it's great you are seeking public opinion... handling open raid loot issues is never easy.<br>
<br>
Everyone attending open raids needs to keep the perspective this is an opportunity created for them by someone with patience.  As long as the raid leader is up front with the rules you have the opportunity for participate or pass ahead of time. <br>
<br>
